[{"question":"And do you think that he should be executed if he\u0027s found guilty?","answer":"I think he should get the exact amount of mercy he gave everyone in that theater.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"Did you feel that in some way he was trying to cheat natural justice?","answer":"The man is a coward.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":49,"aSentId":50},{"question":"Has your view of the death penalty changed because of what happened in Aurora that day?","answer":"I think that in a society that is as violent as ours, we need a lot of different ways to control it and the death penalty is one.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"Have you thought through what the additional torment of a trial, with all the details that may emerge about what happened, not just to your son but the others that lost their lives and were wounded would all come back?","answer":"I can only speak for myself and for my family.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"Are you any nearer having any kind of understanding why Holmes did what he did?","answer":"I have no interest in understanding him.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":64,"aSentId":65},{"question":"What is your view of the gun control debate in America right now?","answer":"I watched the senator today on CNN and it seems like everybody wants to point fingers at everybody else and talked about filibustering.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":67,"aSentId":68},{"question":"What do you say to those politician who say, well, I\u0027d love to -- I\u0027d love to vote for an assault weapons ban but it may cost me my job?","answer":"I say if you have to do your job by lying, you need to get another job.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":84,"aSentId":85},{"question":"Let me ask you first, Dana, we had a pretty civilized discussion today on your radio show, but when you hear a man like Tom Teves speak so eloquently and just desperate for something to happen, what do you say to him?","answer":"It was absolutely heartbreaking.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":111,"aSentId":112},{"question":"Do you really think in your heart that the correct response of a great nation like America to an appalling atrocity like Sandy Hook is to race to sell more guns, more ammunition, and to expand gun rights?","answer":"Well, first of all the murderer in Colorado who killed 12 people should be executed 12 times.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"Now, when you hear those kind of statistics, I suppose the obvious question is this: Does a wrong conviction of somebody -- and we don\u0027t know whether someone being executed -- we have to presume, I would imagine that some may have been before this -- does that on its own not count enough for the desire to execute others?","answer":"I think if we are going to have the conversation about whether or not the death penalty is a legitimate form of punishment, that\u0027s a conversation that folks can have.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":233,"aSentId":234},{"question":"What do you feel about that?","answer":"Look, there is a Second Amendment and it\u0027s important.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":254,"aSentId":255},{"question":"So, finally, and very quickly, Grover Norquist, are you claiming responsibility for the president taking his eye off the ball?","answer":"I think the sequester is responsible for the president not doing as well on basketball as he might.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":292,"aSentId":293},{"question":"And should they think about that going forward?","answer":"It\u0027s a great question.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":361,"aSentId":362},{"question":"Would you jump in a different way if you knew there was a big drop off?","answer":"You know, I think that this thing was just a fluke.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":376,"aSentId":377},{"question":"What is your advice to him going forward in terms of rehabilitation, not just physically, but mentally?","answer":"Well, I think, number one, he has to do his rehab because, you know, when you\u0027re young, and you get hurt, Piers, you try to always rush and come back.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":389,"aSentId":390},{"question":"Have you become homophobic?","answer":"Over I\u0027d say less 10, 12 years, I\u0027ve enjoyed such a degree of independence and freedom, I can basically do whatever I want.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":447,"aSentId":448},{"question":"Are you homophobic?","answer":"Yes, on the -- on the surface it sounds really bad.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":459,"aSentId":460},{"question":"What difference would that make?","answer":"To me it\u0027s an important difference but I don\u0027t think we have time to go into it right now, when you read it in the transcript, which I\u0027d gone back and created, I can do a couple of things to show you and highlight --","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"Are you somebody that objects to a gay lifestyle and to gay marriage?","answer":"If the question is asked to make things simple for the audience and I believe that it is, I\u0027d like to make it even simpler.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":471,"aSentId":472},{"question":"So you\u0027re not homophobic?","answer":"If you want to keep this simple for the audience, let me just give you a straight no, I\u0027m not homophobic.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"Why didn\u0027t you know what you were talking about?","answer":"Because the nature of spontaneous improvisation, I had done it a complete show as truth and then the audience requested reality.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":493,"aSentId":494},{"question":"Are you -- with all the members of the gay community who are outraged by what you said, are you -- are you sorry?","answer":"Yes, I am very much so because what\u0027s being questioned is my support for that community.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":497,"aSentId":498},{"question":"And do you have any problem with gay marriage?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":501,"aSentId":502},{"question":"Do you support it?","answer":"I do.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":503,"aSentId":504},{"question":"So you support full gay rights?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":505,"aSentId":506},{"question":"What do you mean?","answer":"I mean that I have been diligently working for the last five years on a project that is if I have not managed to convince you that I have very much at stake in putting this question to rest is Michelle Shocked homophobic, does Michelle Shocked support the gay community --","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":521,"aSentId":522},{"question":"Do you feel to your satisfaction?","answer":"Well, you\u0027ve answered them very clearly and people can make their own minds up if you mean it.","docId":"130401pmt","qSentId":525,"aSentId":526}]